<subSubSection id="49FE654D8635FF93FF1CF986FBF0F806" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="description">
<paragraph id="015B36C68635FF93FF1CF986FBF0F806" blockId="11.[151,1437,1582,2003]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
DESCRIPTION: Medium-sized species, elongate, not flattened dorso-ventrally. 
<emphasis id="3390EAD48635FF93FBB1F986FBD8F9EF" bold="true" box="[1082,1142,1582,1607]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Male</emphasis>
: Head: Smooth, shining; prominent, longer than wide (
<figureCitation id="99DF2A438635FF93FE60F9FAFDECF9C3" box="[491,578,1618,1643]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-212@12.[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Plochiocoris longicornis. Male. 29, Head; 30, Pronotum; 31, Hemelytra; 32, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternun (Ms); 33, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 34, Detail of left paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947867/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
); antennal segment II sightly less than 4.5x the length of I and longer than length of head + pronotum, with long and erect pilosity. Eyes large and nearly touching ventrally. Labium long, reaching midcoxae; segment I short, not reaching base of antennal segment I; second segment 2.5x longer than third. Thorax: Dorsally covered by erect pilosity. Pronotum with lateral margins slightly bisinuate and not carinate; posterior lobe of pronotum slightly rugose, collar absent (
<figureCitation id="99DF2A438635FF93FCC5F94AFC06F953" box="[846,936,1762,1787]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-212@12.[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Plochiocoris longicornis. Male. 29, Head; 30, Pronotum; 31, Hemelytra; 32, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternun (Ms); 33, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 34, Detail of left paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947867/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Scutellum posteriorly rugose. Hemelytra smooth, not sinuate laterally, subparallel-sided (
<figureCitation id="99DF2A438635FF93FD47F8AEFC8BF8B7" box="[716,805,1798,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-212@12.[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Plochiocoris longicornis. Male. 29, Head; 30, Pronotum; 31, Hemelytra; 32, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternun (Ms); 33, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 34, Detail of left paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947867/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Legs slender and unarmed. Vestigial pads. Ostiolar peritreme straight (
<figureCitation id="99DF2A438635FF93FEFCF882FE46F8EB" box="[375,488,1834,1859]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–16" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1630,1653]" captionTargetBox="[268,1326,195,1607]" captionTargetId="figure-117@6.[261,1326,195,1607]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1–16. Left metapleura of different genera of Lasiochilinae showing the ostiolar peritreme and metapleural microsculpture. 1–2, Plochiocoris (350X and 1000X respectively); 3–5, Eusolenophora (350X, 1000X and 2000X); 6–9, two species of Lasiocolpus showing the small specific differences following a generic pattern: 6–7, L. minor (200X and 1000X) and 8–9, L. sinuaticollis (200X and 1000X); 10–12, Anaelia (200X, 1000X and 2000X); 13–14, Dilasia (200X, and 2000X); 15–16, Lasiochilus (200X, and 2000X)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947861" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947861/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
). Metasternum elongate and apically truncate (
<figureCitation id="99DF2A438635FF93FB9EF882FBC1F8EB" box="[1045,1135,1834,1859]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-212@12.[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Plochiocoris longicornis. Male. 29, Head; 30, Pronotum; 31, Hemelytra; 32, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternun (Ms); 33, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 34, Detail of left paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947867/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
). Apical margin concave. Abdomen: Genitalia with left paramere hook-like, slender, strongly curved (
<figureCitation id="99DF2A438635FF93FB87F8E6FBCCF8CF" box="[1036,1122,1870,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-212@12.[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Plochiocoris longicornis. Male. 29, Head; 30, Pronotum; 31, Hemelytra; 32, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternun (Ms); 33, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 34, Detail of left paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947867/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
); external margin rounded, internal margin deeply sinuate (
<figureCitation id="99DF2A438635FF93FD8CF8DAFDF1F823" box="[519,607,1906,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1923,1946]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-212@12.[340,1247,823,1901]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Plochiocoris longicornis. Male. 29, Head; 30, Pronotum; 31, Hemelytra; 32, Sternum and base of abdomen showing the metasternun (Ms); 33, Pygophore showing left paramere (LP); 34, Detail of left paramere." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947867" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947867/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="3390EAD48635FF93FDFEF8DAFD62F823" bold="true" box="[629,716,1906,1931]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female</emphasis>
: Similar coloration and vestiture to those of male. Head with small eyes not reaching ventral surface; antennal segment II more than 3x as long as I.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49FE654D8635FF93FF4CF812FCD1F87B" box="[199,895,1978,2003]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="015B36C68635FF93FF4CF812FCD1F87B" blockId="11.[151,1437,1582,2003]" box="[199,895,1978,2003]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">DISTRIBUTION: Widely distributed in Western Hemisphere.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49FE654D8632FF94FF4CFF3FFE81FF5F" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="015B36C68632FF94FF4CFF3FFE81FF5F" blockId="12.[151,1437,151,247]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
DISCUSSION: Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="C6E44D458632FF94FD93FF3FFD38FF18" box="[536,662,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Anthocoridae" genus="Dolichiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3390EAD48632FF94FD93FF3FFD38FF18" box="[536,662,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Dolichiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having somewhat larger eyes, with a shorter interocular space, male genitalia strongly curved, a longer penultimate labial segment, and by a smooth and apically concave metasternum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
